trans-unit.source: Represents a <see cref="T:System.Threading.ThreadPriority" /> property (and its value) of a printing system hardware or software component.
trans-unit.target: 인쇄 시스템 하드웨어 또는 소프트웨어 구성 요소의 <see cref="T:System.Threading.ThreadPriority" /> 속성 및 해당 값을 나타냅니다.

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> class.
The name of the <see cref="T:System.Threading.ThreadPriority" /> property that the <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> represents.
Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> class for the specified property.
trans-unit.target: 지정된 속성에 대해 <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> 클래스의 새 인스턴스를 초기화합니다.

trans-unit.source: The `attributeName` should be spelled exactly the same as the name of some particular <xref:System.Threading.ThreadPriority> property of a print system object, including casing.
trans-unit.target: `attributeName` 철자를 사용 해야 몇몇 특정의 이름을 똑같이 <xref:System.Threading.ThreadPriority> 대/소문자를 포함 하는 인쇄 시스템 개체의 속성입니다.

trans-unit.source: For example, the <xref:System.Printing.PrintServer.PortThreadPriority%2A> property of a <xref:System.Printing.PrintServer> object must be spelled "PortThreadPriority", not "ThreadPriority" or "Portthreadpriority".
trans-unit.target: 예를 들어는 <xref:System.Printing.PrintServer.PortThreadPriority%2A> 의 속성을 <xref:System.Printing.PrintServer> "ThreadPriority" 또는 "Portthreadpriority" 아닌지 "PortThreadPriority" 개체를 입력 해야 합니다.

trans-unit.source: The name of the <see cref="T:System.Threading.ThreadPriority" /> property that the <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> represents.
The value of the property that the <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> represents.
Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> class that has the specified value for the specified property.
trans-unit.target: 지정된 속성에 대해 지정된 값을 가지는 <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> 클래스의 새 인스턴스를 초기화합니다.

trans-unit.source: The `attributeName` should be spelled exactly the same as the name of some particular <xref:System.Threading.ThreadPriority> property of a print system object, including casing.
trans-unit.target: `attributeName` 철자를 사용 해야 몇몇 특정의 이름을 똑같이 <xref:System.Threading.ThreadPriority> 대/소문자를 포함 하는 인쇄 시스템 개체의 속성입니다.

trans-unit.source: For example, the <xref:System.Printing.PrintServer.PortThreadPriority%2A> property of a <xref:System.Printing.PrintServer> object must be spelled "PortThreadPriority", not "ThreadPriority" or "Portthreadpriority".
trans-unit.target: 예를 들어는 <xref:System.Printing.PrintServer.PortThreadPriority%2A> 의 속성을 <xref:System.Printing.PrintServer> "ThreadPriority" 또는 "Portthreadpriority" 아닌지 "PortThreadPriority" 개체를 입력 해야 합니다.

trans-unit.source: Provides implicit conversion from a <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> (or from a pointer to such a property) to a <see cref="T:System.Threading.ThreadPriority" /> value.
trans-unit.target: <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> 또는 이러한 속성에 대한 포인터에서 <see cref="T:System.Threading.ThreadPriority" /> 값으로 암시적으로 변환합니다.

trans-unit.source: A pointer to the <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> that is converted.
Provides implicit conversion to a <see cref="T:System.Threading.ThreadPriority" /> value from a pointer to a <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" />.
trans-unit.target: <see cref="T:System.Threading.ThreadPriority" />에 대한 포인터에서 <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> 값으로 암시적으로 변환합니다.

trans-unit.source: Gets or sets the value of the property that the <see cref="T:System.Printing.IndexedProperties.PrintThreadPriorityProperty" /> represents.
